<{markdown}>
Radare is a portable reverse engineering framework that may help you in ...

* Disassembling (and assemble for) many different architectures
* Local natives and remote debuggers (gdb, rap, webui, r2pipe, winedbg, windbg)
* Runs on Linux, *BSD, Windows, OSX, Android, iOS, Solaris and Haiku
* Forensic filesystem and carving for data
* It is written in C and it can be scripted in Python, Javascript, Go and more
* Collaborative analysis using the embedded webserver
* Visualize data structures of several file types
* Patch programs to uncover new features or fix vulnerabilities
* Powerful analysis capabilities to speed up reversing
* Exploitation-related features
<{/markdown}>
